517–Deceased","3 November 1532":"3 November 1532","1532":"1532","1587":"1587","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","Abt 1517":"about 1517","Abt 1538":"about 1538","1517":"1517","Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England":"Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England","Wethersfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Wethersfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Livermore","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: probably a habitational name from Livermere in Suffolk. This is first found in the form <i>Leuuremer</i> (<i>c.</i> 1050), which suggests derivation from Old English <i>lǣfer</i> ‘rush, reed’ + <i>mere</i> ‘lake’. However, later forms consistently show <i>i</i> in the first syllable, suggesting Old English <i>lifer</i> ‘liver’, referring either to the shape of the pond or to the coagulation of the water."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Rebecca","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, from the Latin form of the Hebrew name <i>Rebekah</i>, borne by the wife of Isaac, who was the mother of Esau and Jacob (Genesis 24–27). The Hebrew root occurs in the Bible only in the vocabulary word <i>marbek</i> ‘cattle stall’, and its connection with the name is doubtful. In any case, Rebecca was Aramean, and the name probably has a source in Aramaic. It has always been common as a Jewish name; in England and elsewhere it began to be used also by Christians from the 14th century onwards and especially at the time of the Reformation, when Old Testament names became popular. It was very common among the Puritans in the 17th century, and has enjoyed a tremendous vogue in England since the latter part of the 20th century, among people of many different creeds. In Scotland this is found as an Anglicized form of Beathag ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Rebecca Livermore was born about 1517, in Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Livermore about 1538, in Wethersfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"Abt 1517–":"umbes 1517–Surnud","1517–1587":"1517–1587","1530–1550":"1530–1550","1532–Male":"1532–Surnud","1517–Female":"1517–Surnud","3 November 1532":"3. november 1532","1532":"1532","1587":"1587","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","Abt 1517":"umbes 1517","Abt 1538":"umbes 1538","1517":"1517","Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Thurlow, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England":"Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England","Wethersfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Wethersfield, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1517–":"noin 1517–Kuollut","1517–1587":"1517–1587","1530–1550":"1530–1550","1532–Male":"1532–Kuollut","1517–Female":"1517–Kuollut","3 November 1532":"3. marraskuuta 1532","1532":"1532","1587":"1587","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","Abt 1517":"noin 1517","Abt 1538":"noin 1538","1517":"1517","Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Little Thurlow, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England":"Little Thurlow, Suffolk, England","Wethersfield, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Wethersfield, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1517–":"environ 1517–Décédée","1517–1587":"1517–1587","1530–1550":"1530–1550","1532–Male":"1532–Décédé","1517–Female":"1517–Décédée","3 November 1532":"3 novembre 1532","1532":"1532","1587":"1587","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","Abt 1517":"environ 1517","Abt 1538":"environ 1538","1517":"1517","Hertfordshire, England, United K